Narrator

Vina and I walked into the council chambers. The councilors were already seated and waiting for us.

Player_Romus

"Councilors."

Player_Romus

"Let's keep this meeting quick and concise."

Narrator

The councilors gave me weirdly uncomfortable looks.

Narrator

He gestured at Elena.

Narrator

He then turned to Vina and bowed again.

Hugo Toras

"We also have some news from Mr. Esquibel regarding Pales and the Aureus Gas Field."

Laurento Esquibel

"Your Majesty, the result from the AN Arbitration Committee has just come in."

Laurento Esquibel

"They ruled that both Pales and Rizia are subject to the same international maritime laws, and that the overlap in maritime borders gives both countries equal rights to the field."

Laurento Esquibel

"Very fortunately, the Arbitration Committee rejected Pales' argument about Caleqebiz not having the same maritime radius as mainland Rizia -- acknowledging our right to the Aureus Gas Field."

Player_Romus

"How is that even a resolution?"

Lucita Azaro

"He's not aiding us, Your Majesty. The current maritime laws work in Valgsland's favor."

Laurento Esquibel

"That is correct. Agreeing with the Palesian interpretation would have opened the discussion for the re-evaluation of the Valgish maritime borders as well."

Laurento Esquibel

"As a result, they agreed to divide the gas field in half, granting both of our countries an equal share."

Lucita Azaro

"You are correct, Your Majesty. I still don't see this as a positive outcome."

Player_Romus

"Thank you for your hard work, Mr. Esquibel. Your contributions in our diplomatic efforts deserve credit for this result."

Player_Romus

"I'm not going to share that field with the Duke. That's for sure."

Laurento Esquibel

"According to the maritime borders they established, the field falls inside the Palesian EEZ."

Laurento Esquibel

"The Committee agreed with the Palesian argument about Caleqebiz not having the same maritime radius as mainland Rizia -- acknowledging their sole ownership of the Aureus Gas Field."

Player_Romus

"This is what we feared they would do. We should plan our next steps."

Lucita Azaro

"Pales is playing a dangerous game against us."

Lucita Azaro

"He's not supporting us, Your Majesty. The current maritime laws work in Valgsland's favor."

Laurento Esquibel

"The AN furthermore ruled that the committee members are obliged to enforce the outcome."

Lucita Azaro

"Yes, but we can't let Pales win this fight."

Laurento Esquibel

"I must congratulate you again, Your Majesty, for brokering such a deal and getting the rights to the Aureus Gas Field."

Laurento Esquibel

"Your Majesty, the date of your meeting with Duke Reinhart to officially cede the Aureus field to Pales is confirmed, and will take place in two months."

Laurento Esquibel

"I am hoping this will reflect well for peace in the region."

Player_Romus

"I don't like doing this, but it is a necessary sacrifice."

Lucita Azaro

"With all due respect, Your Majesty, this was hardly a necessary sacrifice."

Lucita Azaro

"The law supports our ownership of at least half of Aureus. Possibly even the entire field--

Laurento Esquibel

"Your comments are appreciated but the deal is already settled, Duchess Azaro."

Player_Romus

"Thank you for your comments, Duchess, but let's move on with the meeting."

Player_Romus

"No. Her comments are not appreciated at all. Are you questioning me, Duchess Azaro?"

Narrator

Lucita had concern in her eyes.

"If there are no other comments on this topic... That was the extent of the news from my side."

"This isn't good situation to be in when we have an energy crisis. The loss of our claim to Aureus could have brought us the much needed energy."

"That settles it, then. If there are no other comments on this topic, we can move on."

"If there are no more comments, let's move on with the meeting."

Laurento Esquibel

"After Princess Vina's successful talks, the date of your meeting with Duke Reinhart to finalize our deal is confirmed, and will take place in two months."

Player_Romus

"I'll be honest, I'm not sure if this was the right decision anymore."

Lucita Azaro

"I agree with that, Your Majesty. We must keep the pressure up."

Elena Werner

"I don't see what good that does for us when we have already acquired half of the rights to the field."

Player_Romus

"You are right. We cannot risk going against the AN. We have to pull back for the time being."

Player_Romus

"You've heard Ms. Werner, we need that energy. We will deploy our navy immediately."

Player_Romus

Lucita Azaro

"Are we forgetting the ties that were found between Pales and the bombing in Zille? What if Reinhart was trying to weaken us to achieve precisely this result?"

Player_Romus

"Well, we all know peace with Pales is not sustainable in the long term... The the time to strike might be now."

Narrator

The councillors went silent. They waited for me to explain what I meant.

Lucita Azaro

"I agree with that, Your Majesty. We must keep the pressure up."

Elena Werner

"As much as the gas in Aureus is incredibly valuable for us, I don't see how we can acquire it after the AN's resolution against us."

Narrator

He fell silent and simply nodded.

Player_Romus

"What did we obtain, really? That whole field is going to be ours. It's time we take Pales back."

Narrator

Laurento looked down at the table. Elena raised an eyebrow.

Hugo Toras

"Ms. Werner has some important reports to share about our current energy situation."

Hugo Toras

"I believe it's time to wrap this up."

Vina Toras

Player_Romus

"No, Vina. We only go against injustice."

Player_Romus

"Yes. But don't worry. They can't do anything to us."

Player_Romus
